&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;We’re a multiple award-winning employer in a luxury senior living community, featuring multiple restaurants and a scratch kitchen, seeking a Full-Time and Part-Time Barback to join our team. In this role, you’ll support bartenders in delivering an exceptional dining and beverage experience by assisting with bar setup, beverage preparation, and maintaining an efficient, organized service area. We offer a competitive hourly rate (no reliance on tips), along with medical and dental insurance options, Paid Time Off, a 401(k), and additional on-the-job perks.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS AND SKILLS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 years of experience as a bartender or mixologist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highschool diploma or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inventory Management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recipe and Menu creation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledgeable in Point of Sale and Inventory Management Systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;English language proficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Preferred:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervisor experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mixology or Bartending Certification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The hourly base wage range provided is a good faith estimate of what Mather reasonably expects to pay for this position at the time of the posting. The actual hourly rate offered will be determined based on a variety of factors, including but not limited to relevant skills, certifications, years of experience, geographic location, and current market conditions. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;At Mather, we are committed to being inclusive, resilient, bold, and impactful—and that includes offering a total rewards experience designed to support our team members. This position may be eligible to participate in Mather’s benefit plan and the Team Member Appreciation Fund, if applicable. Eligibility for benefits is dependent on employment status and hours worked per pay period. Participation in the Team member Appreciation Fund is not guaranteed and may vary based on factors such as hire date and program eligibility requirements. All benefits are subject to change without notice. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Hourly  Pay Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$23 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mather offers a competitive benefits package.*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team members are eligible for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A generous paid time off (PTO) program including vacation days/personal days, sick days, and holidays. This is an “earn-as-you-go” plan that rolls over year to year, offering long- and short-term flexibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A 401(k) program with per pay-period employer match and annual employer contribution (available to those age 21 or better)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Convenient, subsidized parking (or public transportation for certain locations)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wellness Spending Account: up to $300 available annually for Wellness related expenses such as gym memberships, financial planning, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits-eligible team members can take advantage of:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical, dental, and vision plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Parental Leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adoption Assistance Reimbursement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tuition reimbursement for continuing education&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extended illness benefits&lt;/li&g

&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join Our Team as a Skilled Maintenance Professional!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;At The Mather, we’re looking for a dedicated expert to ensure our community buildings and systems operate safely and efficiently for residents, staff, and visitors. In this role, you’ll take the lead on preventative maintenance and repairs for mechanical, electrical, HVAC, plumbing, and life safety systems—keeping everything running smoothly and proactively addressing issues before they become problems. Your expertise will help maintain a healthy, comfortable environment while supporting our commitment to excellence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;This is a full-time, on-site position. Weekend, weeknight, and holiday availability required.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting and/or overseeing preventative maintenance on the mechanical, electrical, HVAC, plumbing systems, fire life safety, and property specific systems which involves normal lubrication, adjustment, cleaning, replacement of consumable parts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs routine lodging inspections and tours as assigned, not limited to air conditioning equipment, furnace systems, generators, and water management systems repairs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs a variety of service work in specialized building systems such as mechanical, electrical/ electronic, hydraulics, machine servicing, to include overseeing generators and UPS maintenance programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducts routine generator tests per building code as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detects malfunctions through observation audio and visual.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assessing and correcting systems to prevent system failures, to include determining solutions to prevent further damage or problems, and identifying resource needs to resolve problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to company processes, procedures, established engineering guidelines, engineering standards and site-specific guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Timely completion of routine repairs, maintenance requests, and work orders throughout the community.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with vendor services management, including building escorts, access, service coordination, and closeout.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend and maintain required training to maintain proficiency and acquire advanced skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provides and coordinates contractors’ support in the execution of building services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains documentation of inspections, deficiencies, through written procedures and workorder database.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains inventory of repair supplies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On-call 24 –7 to handle Emergencies, and other issues that arise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;QUALIFICATIONS AND SKILLS&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years experience in facility/plant engineering and maintenance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand the engineering design and operational aspects of the Base Building and Critical System Support systems and components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thorough knowledge of state and local safety and building codes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective interpersonal, verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of heating, ventilation, and air-conditioning, plumbing, and generators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certification in HVAC (heating, ventilation, and air-conditioning), plumbing, refrigeration, or electrical systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full understanding of Building Management Systems (BMS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of Microsoft Word, Excel, Internet, and Outlook&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Computer proficiency in Microsoft Office and email&lt;/li&gt;
