&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a full-time, hourly position requiring availability to work weeknights, weekends, and holidays as needed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Timely completion of routine repairs, maintenance requests, and work orders throughout the community.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and adjust refrigeration equipment as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform preventative maintenance and adjustments for building, regular wear and tear, windows, doors, locks, and smoke detectors, equipment, and machinery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain community fire and life safety systems and equipment; respond to emergencies according to Mather policies and procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform seasonal exterior maintenance including grounds clean-up, snow removal and salting, maintain light fixtures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detects malfunctions through observation audio and visual.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspects, repair and ensures interior lighting, resident HVAC, elevators, and dining equipment are functioning to code and manufacturer recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducts routine water management systems tests per building code as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with vendor services management, including building escorts, access, service coordination, and closeout.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform/Assist in unlocks, room set-ups/tear downs, receiving/delivery of packages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor the community through regular tours to ensure safety and security of residents, guests, and staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend and maintain required training to maintain proficiency and acquire advanced skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provides and coordinates contractors’ support in the execution of building services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains documentation of inspections, deficiencies, through written procedures and workorder database.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains inventory of cleaning and repair supplies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
