&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are seeking an engaging, safety‑focused Driver to join our luxury senior living community in Tysons.&lt;/strong&gt; This role is essential to delivering an exceptional resident experience by providing safe, reliable, and courteous transportation for residents and guests. The ideal candidate brings a strong customer‑service mindset, takes pride in creating positive and meaningful interactions with residents, and understands the importance of patience, professionalism, and care in a senior living environment. A valid &lt;strong&gt;CDL with passenger endorsement is required&lt;/strong&gt;, as this role is responsible for operating Mather vehicles and ensuring every trip is conducted safely, comfortably, and in accordance with all regulations—while consistently demonstrating Nextraordinary service behaviors.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position is hourly &amp;amp; full-time; weekdays, weekends, and holiday availability required.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer service orientation with excellent interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid CDL Motor Coach, Non-business Type C or Type A with Passenger Endorsement drivers’ license with excellent driving record.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely and efficiently transport residents in Mather vehicles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete required vehicle safety inspections prior to each trip&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain vehicles, mechanically and aesthetically, according to maintenance schedule and as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains a daily check log, service log, and other pertinent records.&lt;/li&gt;
